definition.value: The N-sulfoglucosamine formed by sulfating the amino group of D-glucosamine.
A fructan compound consisting of repeating (2->6)-beta-linked fructofuranose units.
A ribonucleoside composed of a molecule of uracil attached to a ribofuranose moiety via a beta-N(1)-glycosidic bond.

A bisindole alkaloid that is phenol bearing a 3,3-dimethylallyl group at position 4, two methoxy groups at positions 3 and 6, and two indol-3-yl groups at positions 2 and 5. It is a natural product isolated from the sclerotia of Aspergillus orbraceus, with moderate activity against some insects, as well as Gram-positive bacteria.

A member of the class of benzazepines that is 2,3,4,5-tetrahydro-1H-1-benzazepine substituted by oxo groups at positions 2 and 5 and a o-aminobenzamido group at position 4. It is a secondary metabolite found in Aspergillus terreus.
A mannosylinositol-1-phosphoceramide having phytoceramide of unknown length.
A mannosylinositol phosphorylceramide in which the acyl group is hydroxylated at position 2 and the ceramide base is hydroxylated at position 4.
A mannosylinositol phosphorylceramide in which the ceramide base is not hydroxylated at position 4. Major species at pH 7.3.

A polyketide-nonribosomal peptide with an isothiazolinone moiety found in Streptomyces sp. RKND-216. It has a strong selective activity against M. tuberculosis, with no cytotoxicity against mammalian cell lines.
An Ins-1-P-6-Man-1-6-Ins-1-P-Cer in which the acyl group is hydroxylated at position 2 and the ceramide base is hydroxylated at position 4. Major species at pH 7.3.

A penicillanic acid compound having a (6R)-amino substituent. The active nucleus common to all penicillins, it may be substituted at the 6-amino position to form the semisynthetic penicillins, resulting in a variety of antibacterial and pharmacologic characteristics.

A member of the class of epoxides that is (1R,6S)-7-oxabicyclo[4.1.0]hept-3-ene substituted by 3-methylbut-2-en-1-yl, hydroxy, 2-methylbut-1-en-3-yn-4-yl, and hydroxy groups at positions 1, 2R, 3 and 5R. It is a meroterpenoid natural product synthesized by the Ascomycota fungus Biscogniauxia sp.
A cyclic hexapeptide echinocandin antibiotic with a myristoyl side chain. It is produced by a specific strain of Penicillium arenicola and exhibits antimycotic activity.
Any octanoid that is derived from jasmonate.
The organophosphate oxoanion formed from any monolysocardiolipin by deprotonation of the two phospho groups; principal species present at pH 7.3
An enyne that is pentane which carries a triple bond at position 1 and a double bond at position 3.
